uition, and belief, through which the oneiric comes to the center of waking life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDreams in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847209640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438472096423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438472096/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles